    {
      "_id": "EhnkN53VgV3M2sg2",
      "name": "Go for the eyes Boo",
      "type": "feat",
      "system": {
        "source": {
          "custom": "",
          "book": "MaBJoV",
          "page": "68",
          "license": ""
        },
        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Boo is a miniature giant space hamster and has the statistics of a @creature[rat]. As a bonus action, Minsc can talk to Boo and gain the inspiration to go into a berserker fury. While in this berserking fury Minsc gains the following advantages:</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">Minsc has advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Minsc gains a +4 bonus to the damage rolls when using a melee weapon.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Minsc has resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Minsc can make a single melee weapon attack as a bonus</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Minsc can't be &amp;Reference[condition=charmed] or &amp;Reference[condition=frightened] while raging. If Minsc is &amp;Reference[condition=charmed] or &amp;Reference[condition=frightened] when he enters his berserking fury, the effect is suspended for the duration of the rage</li><li class=\"rd__li \">If Minsc drops to 0 hit points while in a berserking fury and doesn't die outright, he can make a [[/save ability=constitution dc=10]] saving throw. If he succeeds, he drops to 1 hit point instead. Each time he uses this feature after the first, the DC increases by 5. After 24 hours, the DC resets to 10.</li></ul></div>",
          "chat": ""
        },
